vulnerability.name: SQL injection
vulnerability.description: SQL injection in a MySQL database was found at: "http://192.168.1.24:9000/post", using HTTP method POST. The sent post-data was: "message=Hello%20World&pseudo=a'b"c'd"" which modifies the "pseudo" parameter. This vulnerability was found in the request with id 625.

header.content: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux i686; rv:6.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/6.0

httpresponse.body: Error: You have an error in your SQL syntax; check the manual that corresponds to your MariaDB server version for the right syntax to use near 'b"c'd"', 'Hello World')' at line 1 Message added successfullygo back to messages

vulnerability.name: Persistent Cross-Site Scripting vulnerability
vulnerability.description: A persistent Cross Site Scripting vulnerability was found by sending "icdhn</->" to the "pseudo" parameter at http://192.168.1.24:9000/post, which is echoed when browsing to http://192.168.1.24:9000/. This vulnerability was found in the requests with ids 730 and 1025.

information.name: Persistent Cross-Site Scripting vulnerability
information.description: A persistent Cross Site Scripting vulnerability was found by sending "icdhn</->" to the "pseudo" parameter at http://192.168.1.24:9000/post, which is echoed when browsing to http://192.168.1.24:9000/. This vulnerability was found in the requests with ids 730 and 1025.
